# ePub format

Format preservation is the single most important invariant. The Python
`epublate` round-trip property test is the spec; the browser port must
honour it.

## Hard rules

- **Placeholders only.** The LLM never sees raw markup. Inline tags
  are encoded as `[[T0]]…[[/T0]]`, void tokens as `[[T0]]`, entities
  as `[[T0]]`. The `inline_skeleton` records the original tag + attrs
  so re-assembly is lossless.
- **`applyParts(host, [placeholderize(host)])` is identity** on the
  host's serialized form. Any change to the segmenter must keep this
  property. There's a fast-check property test that gates regressions.
- **One placeholder open ↔ one close**, exactly. Sentence splits
  never land inside an open pair (`safeSplitPoints` enforces this).
  Unmatched placeholders ⇒ `EpubFormatError`.
- **Don't drop comments / PIs by surprise.** The current segmenter
  drops them deliberately to mirror Python; document any new behaviour
  in the file docstring.

## Working with images

- Inline `<img>` tokens are kept in `inline_skeleton` and resolved at
  render time via `ImageResolver` (`src/lib/preview.tsx`). Don't
  hardcode object URLs into segment text.
- Standalone images (image-only `<p>` / `<figure>`) live outside the
  segment table — surface them to the Reader via
  `findStandaloneImages` rather than synthesising fake segments.

## Reassembly

- `reassembleChapter` runs the same validators that intake uses. If
  you add a new segment field that affects layout, pipe it through
  `Segment` *and* the validator.

## Workers (ZIP I/O only)

- ZIP decompression / re-compression run in
  `src/workers/epub.worker.ts`, called via
  `src/workers/epub.client.ts`. Don't add direct `JSZip.loadAsync` /
  `zip.generateAsync` calls in the loader / writer — the client has
  both worker and inline fallbacks already wired.
- The worker boundary is structured-clone only. Pass `Map<path, …>`
  with `Uint8Array` / `string` values and `ArrayBuffer`
  transferables. No DOM nodes, no functions, no class instances.
- `DOMParser` / `XMLSerializer` stay on the main thread —
  browser-worker compatibility is unreliable. Only CPU-bound,
  string/bytes-in / string/bytes-out work belongs in
  `src/workers/`.
- The inline fallback path MUST be byte-equivalent to the worker
  path. The `src/workers/epub.client.test.ts` round-trip is the
  contract.
